3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FapfL7ULrQ-I%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Embracing%20chaos%2C%20inquiry%20over%20advocacy%2C%20poking%20the%20bear%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cimpact%2C%20impact%2C%20impact%E2%80%9D%20%7C%20Vlad%20Loktev%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e6f2278d-1339-49f3-8399-ba0c879a2a9b%5C%22%3EEmbrace%20the%20chaos%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20chaos%20in%20the%20workplace%20usually%20reads%20as%20scary%20to%20most%20people%2C%20Loktev%20said%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bis%20actually%20great.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20you%20want%20to%20create%20chaos%20in%20an%20organization%20to%20push%20the%20organization%20to%20think%20creatively%20and%20to%20actually%20make%20leaps%20in%20product%20development%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20recalled%20Chesky%20telling%20him%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20I%20just%20don't%20feel%20good.%20Something%20feels%20off.%26quot%3B%20Although%20Loketev%20noted%20that%20their%20booking%20numbers%20were%20up%20and%20things%20appeared%20to%20be%20running%20smoothly%2C%20the%20CEO%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3BThings%20are%20just%20too%20calm.%20I%20don't%20like%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20picked%20an%20important%20project%20that%20was%20scheduled%20for%20a%20multi-week%20design%20process%20and%20building%20timeline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20said%2C%20'Yeah%2C%20I%20don't%20care%20about%20any%20of%20that.%20We're%20going%20to%20design%20this%20in%2024%20hours%2C'%26quot%3B%20Loktev%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20was%20just%20mind%20blown.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20eruption%20of%20the%20neat%20time%20flow%20originally%20planned%2C%20they%20did%20manage%20to%20complete%20the%20design%20in%20a%20little%20over%20a%20day.%20Loktev%20said%20he%20learned%20from%20how%20Chesky%20strategically%20inserted%20some%20disarray%20into%20an%20otherwise%20calm%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20chaos%20forced%20us%2C%20with%20our%20artificial%20time%20constraint%2C%20to%20dial%20up%20our%20intuition%20and%20to%20think%20a%20bit%20more%20creatively%20than%20maybe%20we%20would%20have%20in%20the%20past%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2262cb1b81-fc27-46d8-a514-007cea92f21b%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20continue%20growing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20starting%20as%20a%20product%20manager%2C%20Loktev%20held%20several%20roles%20during%20his%20decade%20at%20Airbnb%2C%20from%20director%20of%20product%20to%20VP%20and%20GM%20of%20Airbnb%20Plus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20is%2C%20every%20three%20to%20six%20months%2C%20my%20job%20changed%2C%26quot%3B%20Loktev%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20as%20soon%20as%20he%20got%20comfortable%20in%20a%20position%2C%20everything%20familiar%20would%20%26quot%3Bbreak.%26quot%3B%20From%20different%20projects%20and%20hiring%20processes%20to%20how%20he%20would%20spend%20his%20time%2C%20Loktev%20said%20he%20would%20have%20to%20%26quot%3Breinvent%26quot%3B%20himself%20in%20each%20new%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20thing%20that%20I've%20learned%20is%20you've%20got%20to%20ask%20for%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20a%20village%2C%20right%3F%20You%20can't%20just%20get%20there%20by%20yourself.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20he%20learned%20it%20from%20Chesky%2C%20whom%20Lokteve%20said%20would%20continuously%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20six%20months%2C%20it%20was%20like%20a%20different%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20a%20lot%20of%20his%20secret%20sauce%20is%20not%20being%20afraid%20to%20ask%20people%20for%20help%20who%20are%20experts%20in%20the%20thing%20that%20you're%20trying%20to%20learn.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20motto%20is%2C%20%26quot%3BAsk%20for%20the%20impossible%2C%20and%20sometimes%20you're%20going%20to%20be%20surprised%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c610abc4-4411-4808-afe9-2fdb34c83016%5C%22%3ETop-down%20leadership%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20negative%20connotations%20of%20top-down%20leadership%20can%20often%20invoke%20an%20image%20of%20a%20leader%20making%20all%20the%20decisions%20%26quot%3Bin%20an%20ivory%20tower%26quot%3B%20while%20everyone%20else%20sits%20powerless%20below.%20Loketev%20said%20that%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20in%20Airbnb%20%E2%80%94%20this%20is%20a%20common%20misconception%20of%20the%20top-down%20organizational%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20actually%20a%20reality%20of%20top-down%2C%26quot%3B%20Loketev%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20that%20room%20where%20we%20made%20many%20of%20the%20hard%20decisions%20with%20Brian%2C%20the%20reality%20was%20he%20asked%20a%20shit%20ton%20of%20questions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20VP%20said%20Chesky%20would%20refrain%20from%20immediately%20advocating%20for%20his%20own%20opinions%20but%20rather%20would%20listen%20and%20often%20change%20his%20mind%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20as%20a%20leader%20at%20Airbnb%20for%20so%20long%2C%20I%20never%20felt%20like%20I%20wasn't%20listened%20to%20or%20like%20he%20was%20just%20making%20these%20random%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20always%20had%20an%20ability%20to%20influence%20and%20an%20ability%20to%20voice%20where%20I%20felt%20like%20the%20company%20should%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChesky's%20involved%20approach%20has%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-everyone-in-tech-talking-founder-mode-paul-graham-chesky-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einspired%20recent%20critique%3C%2Fa%3E%20around%20Silicon%20Valley's%20modus%20operandi