20children's%20college%20educations%20is%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbasic-income-gbi-ubi-low-income-americans-afford-housing-food-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20possible%20with%20the%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20we%20currently%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9fa14a4-2457-484b-9fb4-44d5db8e7020%5C%22%3EWe%20both%20paid%20for%20our%20college%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20my%20husband%20nor%20I%20come%20from%20families%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearned-thousands-in-scholarships-graduated-college-debt-free-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecould%20pay%20for%20our%20college%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nor%20did%20it%20ever%20cross%20our%20minds%20that%20it%20might%20even%20be%20an%20option.%20My%20husband%20comes%20from%20a%20family%20of%20small-town%20farmers%20and%20my%20parents%20were%20first-generation%20college%20graduates%20without%20any%20extra%20money%20to%20spare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20both%20had%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fbest-scholarship-websites%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20scholarships%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20loans%20to%20pay%20for%20our%20college%20%E2%80%94%20we%20worked%20as%20teenagers%2C%20my%20husband%20qualified%20for%20the%20PELL%20grant%2C%20and%20I%20chose%20a%20school%20that%20offered%20full-tuition%20scholarships%20to%20high%20school%20valedictorians%20(and%20succeeded%20in%20becoming%20valedictorian%20to%20secure%20my%20free%20tuition).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20recognize%20that%20times%20are%20very%2C%20very%20different%20now%2C%20but%20we%20both%20believe%20that%20there%20are%20creative%20ways%20that%20teens%20can%20at%20least%20partly%20fund%20their%20college%20degrees%20outside%20of%20family%20money%2C%20and%20we%20plan%20to%20encourage%20our%20children%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-paid-for-college-with-scholarships-and-grants-heres-how-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efind%20ways%20to%20pay%20for%20their%20future%20educations%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d58c3dfe-d67a-42cf-9842-925182fb7f2a%5C%22%3EOur%20oldest%20is%20taking%20advantage%20of%20early%20college%20programs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20I%20attended%20an%20orientation%20with%20my%2016-year-old%20for%20her%20early%20college%20program.%20I%20was%20not%20familiar%20with%20early%20college%20programs%2C%20but%20they've%20become%20popular%20in%20our%20local%20area%2C%20both%20for%20the%20support%20they%20can%20offer%20teens%20transitioning%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffinancial-planner-balancing-saving-college-retirement-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20and%20the%20cost%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20can%20offer.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-cant-afford-10000-summer-pre-college-programs-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEarly%20college%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20vary%20by%20state%2C%20but%20most%20work%20through%20a%20partnership%20with%20a%20local%20college%20and%20offer%20high%20schoolers%20a%20chance%20to%20take%20modified%20college%20courses%20alongside%20their%20high%20school%20curriculum%20for%20free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20in%20the%20program%20take%20an%20additional%20year%20of%20high%20school%20that%2C%20's%20a%20full%20college%20course%20load%2C%20and%20then%20graduate%20high%20school%20with%20up%20to%2060%20college%20credits%2C%20sometimes%20enough%20for%20a%20full%20associate's%20degree.%20The%20program%20then%20works%20with%20the%20student%20to%20transition%20them%20onto%20the%20next%20step%2C%20including%20transferring%20those%20credits%20to%20a%20four-year%20school%20if%20that's%20their%20wish.%20My%20daughter%20is%20excited%20about%20the%20program%20and%20took%20the%20steps%20to%20sign%20up%20for%20it%20on%20her%20own%2C%20and%20I%20know%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20is%20driven%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20she%20knows%20we%20can't%20pay%20for%20her%20college.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228bf46b02-6fce-4f84-89b3-95867a772473%5C%22%3EWe%20have%20small%20savings%20for%20each%20child%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20our%20choice%20to%20have%20a%20large%20family%2C%20and%20despite%20having%20children%20young%20(our%20first%20was%20born%20while%20we%20were%20still%20college%20students)%20and%20having%20limited%20financial%20resources%20from%20the%20start%2C%20I%20have%20done%20my%20best%20to%20have%20some%20kind%20of%20savings%20for%20my%20children.%20I%20started%20savings%20accounts%20for%20each%20of%20them%20after%20they%20were%20born%20and%20set%20up%20automatic%20transfers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20the%20years%2C%20sometimes%2C%20it%20has%20only%20been%20%2425%20bucks%20every%20quarter%20that%20we%20could%20contribute%2C%20but%20in%20my%20mind%2C%20it%20would%20be%20better%20than%20nothing.%20It's%20my%20hope%20that%20even%20a%20small%20amount%20will%20help%20them%20when%20they%20are%20ready%20for%20the%20next%20steps%20after%20high%20school%2C%20even%20if%20it%20only%20covers%20books.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223eafb941-b20a-4b90-97e5-e80ab2d38a08%5C%22%3EI%20just%20opened%20a%20529%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20when%20my%20daughter%20turned%2015%2C%20it%20really%20hit%20me%20how%20fast%20college%20was%20approaching%2C%20so%20I%20panicked%20a%20little%20about%20how%20we%20could%20help%20her.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%20early%20college%20program%2C%20I%20took%20the%20small%20amount%20of%20savings%20we%20did%20have%20for%20her%20and%20opened%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-parents-should-know-about-529s-and-how-use-them-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E529%20education%20account%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20plans%20are%20state-specific%20but%20are%20interest-earning%20savings%20accounts%20specifically%20for%20education%20costs.%20Alt