20814%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20has%20engendered%20an%20asinine%20outrage%20-%20rarely%20are%20outrages%20worth%20the%20GBs%20spent%20on%20them%20these%20days%20-%20involving%20names.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetflix%20India's%20head%20has%20been%20summoned%20by%20the%20centre%20because%20some%20busybodies%2C%20ignoring%20historical%20facts%2C%20have%20taken%20umbrage%20to%20the%20non-Muslim%20names%20of%20the%20Pakistani%20Muslim%20hijackers%20of%20the%20fated%20Air%20India%20flight%20number%20IC814.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty-five%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20had%20to%20release%20Masood%20Azhar%20-%20now%20the%20boss%20of%20Jaish%20e%20Muhammad%20-%20along%20with%20two%20other%20terrorists%20in%20a%20bid%20to%20save%20191%20passengers%20and%20crew%20members.%20This%20happened%20after%20negotiating%20for%20seven%20days%20with%20five%20men%20of%20the%20Harkat%20ul%20Islam%20terror%20outfit%2C%20codenamed%20'Chief'%2C%20'Burger'%2C%20'Shankar'%2C%20'Bhola'%20and%20'Doctor'%2C%20who%20hijacked%20the%20plane%20right%20after%20it%20took%20off%20from%20Kathmandu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Bigger%20Question%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Internet%20has%20been%2C%20predictably%2C%20awash%20with%20angry%20responses%20to%20the%20series%20using%20these%20codenames.%20It%20is%20the%20same%20people%20who%20are%20upset%20that%20Muslim%20actors%2C%20artists%2C%20et%20al%2C%20use%20%26quot%3BHindu%26quot%3B%20names%20for%20popularity.%20This%20entire%20'controversy'%20could%20have%20easily%20been%20ignored%20had%20it%20not%20led%20to%20top-down%20interventions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERIP%2C%20freedom%20of%20speech%2C%20expression%2C%20and%20everything%20else%20with%20it%20when%20even%20the%20facts%20have%20to%20surrender%20to%20sentiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20here%20is%20the%20bigger%20question%20about%20names-what%20is%2C%20indeed%2C%20in%20a%20name%3F%20The%20recent%20outrage%20is%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20the%20situation%20when%20many%20clapped%20enthusiastically%20in%20the%20cinema%20halls%20when%20Siddharth%20Malhotra%20played%20Captain%20Vikram%20Batra%2C%20the%20hero%20of%20the%20Kargil%20war%2C%20fought%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20barely%20six%20months%20before%20IC-814%20was%20hijacked.%20Captain%20Batra%2C%20before%20he%20was%20killed%20in%20action%2C%20went%20by%20an%20alias%20Shershah.%20Now%20think%20about%20Iftikhar%2C%20another%20film%2C%20another%20alias%20used%20by%20an%20army%20officer%2C%20Maj%20Mohit%20Sharma.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20People%20Take%20Aliases%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20norm%2C%20not%20an%20aberration%2C%20for%20Indian%20armed%20forces%20personnel%20to%20use%20aliases%20during%20counter-insurgency%20and%20conflict%20situations.%20Their%20identity%20becomes%20the%20Trojan%20horse%20to%20infiltrate%20and%20destroy%20the%20enemy's%20defences.%20This%20is%20precisely%20what%20the%20enemy%20does%2C%20too.%20The%20entire%20breadth%20of%20tactical%20communication%20is%20predicated%20on%20aliases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConcluding%20a%20study%20to%20assess%20%26quot%3Bimplicit%20and%20explicit%20attitudes%20toward%20Muslims%20and%20Christians%20within%20a%20predominantly%20Christian%20sample%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20juxtaposing%20names%20with%20adjectives%2C%20researchers%20Wade%20C.%20Rowatt%2C%20Lewis%20M.%20Franklin%20and%20Marla%20Cotton%20stated%20in%202005%2C%20%26quot%3Bself-reported%20attitudes%20toward%20Christians%20were%20more%20positive%20than%20their%20self-reported%20attitudes%20towards%20Muslims%26quot%3B.%20This%20is%20consistent%20with%20social%20identity%20theory.%20The%20findings%20of%20any%20such%20study%20are%20going%20to%20be%20similar%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArmed%20forces%20personnel%20engaging%20in%20covert%20operations%20know%20it%20is%20easier%20to%20blend%20in%20when%20your%20name%20does%20not%20have%20unpleasant%20associations.%20And%20so%20do%20terrorists.%20The%20only%20people%20ignoring%20it%20are%20the%20frenzied%20internet%20warriors.%20But%20that's%20not%20surprising.%20The%20name%20'conspiracy'%20is%20just%20another%20quick-to-find%20trigger.%20This%20time%2C%20however%2C%20the%20trigger%20probably%20masks%20a%20sense%20of%20institutional%20shame.%20The%20fact%20that%20Masood%20Azhar%20is%20still%20free%20and%20conveniently%20plotting%20and%20carrying%20out%20terrorist%20actions%20against%20India%20is%20an%20injury%20to%20the%20insult%20that%20the%20IC-814%20hijacking%20was.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Should%20Really%20Rattle%20Us%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20truly%20merits%20outrage%20is%20how%20the%20systems%20disallowed%20a%20timely%20follow-up%20on%20multiple%20intelligence%20warnings.%20Let's%20outrage%20how%2C%20despite%20endless%20domestic%20brouhaha%20over%20the%20role%20of%20Pakistan%20in%20the%20hijacking%2C%20we%20are%20yet%20to%20mount%20any%20case%20against%20the%20inter-services%20intelligence%20(ISI)%20agency%20in%20a%20global%20forum.%20Let%20us%20also%20express%20our%20outrage%2C%20since%20we%20are%20tireless%2C%20about%20how%20our%20security%20infrastructure%20has%20a%20thousand%20leaks%2C%20ensuring%20no%20timely%20action%20could%20be%20taken%20before%20the%20flight%20took%20off%2C%20first%20from%20Kathmandu%20and%20later%20from%20Amritsar.%20As%20senior%20police%20officer%20KPS%20Gill%20noted%20in%20his%20assessment%20of%20the%20event%2C%20even%20the%20telephone%20numbers%20of%20the%20Crisis%20Management%20Group%20listed%20at%20the%20Delhi%20Airport%20were%20incorrect.%20Let's%20outrage%20for%20accountability%20and%20systemic%20overhaul.%20Let's%20outrage%20because%20we%20do%20not%20have%20any%20coherent%20strategy%20to%20deal%20with%20our%20enemies%2C%20so%20we%20only%20either%20respond%20to%20the%20stimuli%20or%20busy%20ourselves%20fighting%20strawmen.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20outrage%20will%20not%20happen%20simply%20because%20it%20does%20not%20suit%20the%20narrative.%20Calling%20names%20and%20calling%20out%20for%20names%20are%20easier%20when%20faced%20with%20uncomfortable%20truths.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Nishtha%20Gautam%20is%20a%20Delhi-based%20author%20and%20academic.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725451860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F4qj3ne88_ic-814_625x300_04_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-ic-814-whats-in-a-name-just-a-reason-to-outrage-6489378%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20truly%20merits%20outrage%20is%20how%20the%20systems%20disallowed%20a%20timely%20follow-up%20on%20multiple%20intelligence%20warnings.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-ic-814-whats-in-a-name-just-a-reason-to-outrage-6489378%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Will%20King%20Charles%20abdicate%3F%20Here's%20what%20Queen%20Camilla%20said%20on%20his%20health%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725451549000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113065183%2Cimgsize-1357499.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fwill-king-charles-abdicate-heres-what-queen-camilla-said-on-his-health%2Farticleshow%2F113065120.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%E2%80%8BA%20Royal%20insider%20said%20it%20would%20be%20the%20%26quot%3Bbest%20decision%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20King%20to%20step%20down%20now.%20%E2%80%9CNo%20one%20expects%20his%20%5BKing%20Charles%5D%20reign%20to%20last%20much%20longer%2C%20especially%20because%20his%20health%20could%20take%20a%20dramatic%20turn%20for%20the%20worse%20at%20any%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20insider%20was%20by%20In%20Touch.%20%E2%80%9CStepping%20down%20now%20would%20be%20the%2