2C%20holds%20a%20wealth%20of%20records%20and%20a%20lengthy%20list%20of%C2%A0landmarks.%20From%20the%20ruler's%20long%20and%20elaborate%20official%20name%E2%80%94Sultan%20Haji%20Hassanal%20Bolkiah%20Mu'izzaddin%20Waddaulah%20ibni%20Al-Marhum%20Sultan%20Haji%20Omar%20%E2%80%98Ali%20Saifuddien%20Sa'adul%20Khairi%20Waddien%E2%80%94to%20his%20claim%20as%20one%20of%20the%20wealthiest%20rulers%20and%20the%20world's%20longest-reigning%20monarch%2C%20Brunei%20consistently%20makes%20its%20mark%20in%20the%20record%20books.%20However%2C%20this%20former%20British%20protectorate%2C%20which%20gained%20full%20independence%20in%201984%2C%20is%20more%20than%20its%20oil%20riches%20and%20opulence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBonded%20Through%20Language%20and%20History%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20is%20officially%20known%20as%20Negara%20Brunei%20Darussalam%20in%20its%20official%20language%2C%20Malay%2C%20or%20Bahasa%20Melayu.%20The%20Malay%20term%20%E2%80%9CBahasa%E2%80%9D%20originates%20from%20the%20Sanskrit%20word%20%E2%80%9Cbhasha%E2%80%9D%2C%20meaning%20language%2C%20while%20%E2%80%9CNegara%E2%80%9D%20is%20derived%20from%20the%20Sanskrit%20word%20%E2%80%9CNagara%2FNagari%E2%80%9D%2C%20meaning%20city.%20Brunei's%20capital%2C%20Bandar%20Seri%20Begawan%2C%20was%20renamed%20in%201970%20from%20its%20previous%20name%2C%20Bandar%20Brunei%2C%20to%20honour%20the%20country's%20former%20ruler%2C%20Sultan%20Omar%20Ali%20Saifuddien%20III%2C%20whose%20name%20draws%20from%20the%20Sanskrit%20term%20%E2%80%9CShri%20Bhagwan%E2%80%9D%2C%20meaning%20Lord%20Almighty%20or%20%E2%80%98the%20Blessed%20One'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20a%20century%20ago%2C%20a%20historical%20connection%20to%20India%20emerged%20when%20British%20soldier%20and%20sojourner%20James%20Brooke%2C%20born%20in%20Bandel%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20was%20granted%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20Brunei's%20territory%20in%201841%20by%20Sultan%20Omar%20Ali%20Saifuddin%20II%20for%20quelling%20a%20rebellion.%20Brooke%20later%20received%20the%20title%20of%20Rajah%E2%80%94derived%20from%20the%20Sanskrit%20word%20for%20King%E2%80%94of%20Sarawak%2C%20now%20a%20state%20in%20Malaysia%2C%20and%20became%20known%20as%20the%20White%20Rajah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot-So-Proactive%20Engagement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20recent%20visit%20to%20Bandar%20Seri%20Begawan%2C%20particularly%20at%20the%20Royal%20Regalia%20Museum%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20capital%2C%20I%20spotted%20a%20photograph%20of%20an%20Indian%20teacher%20dressed%20in%20a%20saree.%20The%20image%20featured%20the%20current%20ruler%20from%20his%20student%20days%20at%20Sultan%20Omar%20Ali%20Saifuddien%20College%20in%201964.%20Surprisingly%2C%20amidst%20the%20museum's%20glittering%20collection%20of%20royal%20regalia%E2%80%94showcasing%20exquisite%20state%20gifts%20from%20several%20heads%20of%20state%20and%20top%20ministers%20from%20countries%20like%20China%2C%20Singapore%2C%20Thailand%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20the%20USA%E2%80%94the%20Indian%20gift%20was%20attributed%20to%20a%20former%20Indian%20High%20Commissioner%20and%20not%20a%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPM's%20Historic%20Visit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELinguistically%20and%20historically%2C%20Brunei%20and%20India%20share%20a%20long-standing%20connection.%20However%2C%20their%20geopolitical%20relations%20require%20a%20boost%2C%20particularly%20as%20India%20aims%20to%20enhance%20its%20role%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region.%20Notably%2C%20no%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20had%20visited%20Brunei%20for%20a%20bilateral%20discussion%20before%20Narendra%20Modi%20embarked%20on%20a%20trip%20as%20part%20of%20his%20proactive%20Act%20East%20policy.%20Although%20Brunei's%20Sandhurst-educated%20Sultan%20has%20made%20four%20visits%20to%20India%20since%20the%20establishment%20of%20diplomatic%20ties%20in%201984%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Manmohan%20Singh%20was%20the%20only%20Indian%20leader%20to%20visit%20Brunei%20for%20two%20back-to-back%20multilateral%20events%E2%80%94the%2011th%20ASEAN-India%20Summit%20and%20the%208th%20East%20Asia%20Summit%E2%80%94held%20in%20Bandar%20Seri%20Begawan%20in%20October%202013.%20The%20transition%20from%20the%20earlier%20Look%20East%20policy%20to%20a%20more%20active%20Act%20East%20policy%20began%20after%20Modi%20took%20office%20in%202014%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20first-ever%20high-level%20bilateral%20visit%20to%20Brunei%20by%20Vice-President%20Hamid%20Ansari%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOil-Driven%20Economic%20Partnerships%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBrunei%20boasts%20a%20high-income%2C%20oil-rich%20economy.%20Despite%20the%20pandemic's%20temporary%20stagnation%20of%20its%20oil-driven%20sector%2C%20Brunei%20maintains%20a%20currency%20valued%20at%20par%20with%20Singapore's%20dollar%2C%20which%20is%20also%20widely%20used%20in%20the%20country.%20India's%20primary%20exports%20to%20Brunei%20include%20automobiles%2C%20transport%20equipment%2C%20rice%2C%20and%20spices.%20Conversely%2C%20India%20is%20one%20of%20Brunei's%20largest%20importers%20of%20crude%20oil%2C%20with%20annual%20imports%20valued%20at%20approximately%20%24500-600%20million.%20At%20the%20recently%20opened%20Brunei%20Energy%20Hub%2C%20an%20interactive%20oil%20and%20gas%20museum%20in%20Bandar%20Seri%20Begawan%2C%20the%20country's%20oil%20and%20gas%20development%20timeline%20highlights%20India%20as%20one%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Ckey%20customers%E2%80%9D%20of%20Brunei%20Shell%20Petroleum%20(BSP)%2C%20a%20joint%20venture%20between%20the%20Government%20of%20Brunei%20and%20Shell%2C%20noting%20the%20first%20delivery%20of%20oil%20cargo%20to%20India%20in%202003%2C%20with%20approximately%2025%2C000%20barrels%20supplied%20each%20year%20thereafter.%20A%20significant%20portion%20of%20Brunei's%20Indian%20diaspora%2C%20nearly%2015%2C000%2C%20primarily%20works%20in%20the%20oil%20and%20gas%20sector%2C%20with%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20unskilled%20Indian%20workers%20entering%20the%20construction%20and%20other%20unorganised%20sectors%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEye%20On%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20161%20kilometres%20of%20coastline%20along%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20Brunei%2C%20home%20to%20nearly%204%2C50%2C000%20people%2C%20holds%20both%20geographical%20and%20geopolitical%20significance%20in%20the%20Indo-Pacific%20region.%20The%20nation%20is%20a%20silent%20claimant%20to%20this%20contested%20maritime%20area%2C%20maintaining%20a%20delicate%20balance%20in%20its%20relations%20with%20China%20and%20other%20ASEAN%20neighbours%2C%20despite%20China's%20growing%20assertiveness%20in%20the%20region.%20In%20May%20of%20this%20year%2C%20Brunei%20signed%20a%20maritime%20cooperation%20agreement%20with%20the%20Philippines%2C%20which%20has%20recently%20taken%20a%20stand%20against%20China's%20aggression%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20officially%20referring%20to%20the%20area%20near%20its%20coastline%20as%20the%20West%20Philippine%20Sea.%20Simultaneously%2C%20the%20Islamic%20nation%20has%20strengthened%20its%20defence%20ties%20with%20India%20over%20the%20years.%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi's%20visit%20is%20anticipated%20to%20solidify%20this%20relationship%2C%20especially%20in%20light%20of%20China's%20expanding%20influence%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECulinary%20Connection%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20Brunei's%20population%20comprises%20more%20than%2010%25%20Chinese%20immigrants%2C%20with%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20their%20ancestors%20hailing%20from%20the%20Taiwanese%20islands%20of%20Kinmen.%20This%20group%20fled%20heavy%20shelling%20by%20China%20during%20the%20First%20and%20Second%20Taiwan%20Strait%20crises%20in%20the%201950s.%20While%20enjoying%20traditional%20%E2%80%98roti%20kacang%20kahwin'%20and%20%E2%80%98roti%20kuning%20kahwin'%20(the%20word%20%26quot%3Broti%26quot%3B%20means%20bread%20in%20Malay%2C%20like%20in%20Hindi)%20at%20Chop%20Jing%20Chew%2C%20a%20historic%20bakery%20and%20eatery%20in%20Bandar%20Seri%20Begawan%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20to%20find%20that%20the%20Chinese-immigrant-owned%20establishment%20is%20run%20entirely%20by%20Indian%20staff.%20My%20culinary%20exploration%20also%20revealed%20that%20one%20of%20Brunei's%20most%20popular%20and%20top-rated%20(by%20Tripadvisor)%20restaurants%2C%20Riyaz%2C%20located%20in%20a%20prominent%20hotel%2C%20is%20managed%20by%20a%20team%20of%20Indian%20chefs%20and%20hospitality%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBollywood's%20Soft%20Power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20visit%20to%20another%20well-regarded%20restaurant%2C%20Soto%20Pabo%2C%20along%20the%20Brunei%20riverfront%2C%20highlighted%20Brunei's%20deep-rooted%20cross-cultural%20connection%20with%20India.%20I%20encountered%20two%20elderly%20Bruneians%20jamming%20with%20a%20guitar%2C%20who%20greeted%20me%20with%20a%20warm%20%26quot%3BNamaste%26quot%3B%20in%20fluent%20Hindi.%20After%20introducing%20myself%20and%20joining%20their%20gathering%2C%20one%20of%20them%2C%20Hajiali%2C%20told%20me%20that%20he%20had%20studied%20in%20Lucknow%20for%20a%20year%20in%20the%201970s.%20The%20septuagenarian%2C%20together%20with%20his%20friend%20and%20the%20eatery's%20owner's%20octogenarian%20father-in-law%2C%20entertained%20us%20with%20a%20medley%20of%20classic%20Bollywood%20songs.%20I%20was%20captivated%20by%20the%20nostalgic%20tunes%20of%20Mukesh's%20%E2%80%9CSawan%20Ka%20Mahina%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kishore%20Kumar's%20%E2%80%9CZindagi%20Ek%20Safar%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20Mohammad%20Rafi's%20%E2%80%9CJo%20Wada%20Kiya.%E2%80%9D%20A%20little%20later%2C%20after%20savouring%20their%20signature%20Ambuyat%20set%E2%80%94a%20traditional%20Bruneian%20meal%E2%80%94I%20took%20a%20ferry%20to%20Kampung%20Ayer%2C%20a%20traditional%20water%20village%20near%20the%20capital.%20As%20we%20sailed%20through%20the%20mangroves%20populated%20with%20long-nosed%20proboscis%20monkeys%C2%A0(featured%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ci%3ETintin%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3Eadventure%2C%20Flight%20714)%2C%20the%20boatman%20began%20singing%20%E2%80%9CKuch%20Kuch%20Hota%20Hai%E2%80%9D%20upon%20learning%20my%20nationality.%20This%20experience%20reminded%20me%20of%20my%20travels%20to%20Timor-Leste%20and%20Indonesia%2C%20where%20locals%20also%20fondly%20recalled%20the%20Bollywood%20classic.%20It%20was%20a%20profound%20demonstration%20of%20India's%20enduring%20soft%20power%20through%20Bollywood.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20heartening%20to%20see%20the%20influence%20of%20Indian%20culture%20in%20Brunei%20even%20before%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi's%20visit%2C%20India%20must%20further%20engage%20with%20this%20small%20yet%20affluent%20nation%20to%20enhance%20its%20strategic%20position%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Suvam%20Pal%20works%20as%20a%20broadcast%20journalist%20with%20TaiwanPlus%20news%20channel%20in%20Taipei)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725446880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F6qgu0aqg_brunei_625x300_04_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Frafi-songs-to-roti-bruneis-deep-cultural-connect-with-india-6488122%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20it's%20heartening%20to%20see%20the%20influence%20of%20Indian%20culture%20in%20Brunei%20even%20before%20Prime%20Minister%20Modis%20visit%2C%20India%20must%20further%20engage%20with%20this%20small%20yet%20affluent%20nation%20to%20enhance%20its%20strategic%20position%20in%20the%20region.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Frafi-songs-to-roti-bruneis-deep-cultural-connect-with-india-6488122%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Raygun%20apologises%20to%20Australian%20breakdancing%20community%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725446664000%2C%22visu